4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, Class 2 municipalities may
6 put a lien on real properties for unpaid municipal code
7 violations and foreclose on those properties with
8 unpaid municipal code liens.
9 This bill would revise the foreclosure process
10 for Class 2 municipalities by removing the requirement
11 to notify the State of Alabama and all other taxing
12 officials in the municipality's jurisdiction of the
13 municipality's intent to complete a municipal lien
14 foreclosure sale. This bill would authorize the
15 municipality to create and adopt its own petition for
16 judicial in rem foreclosure by local ordinance and
17 would remove the statutory petition and deed language.
18 This bill would shorten the time periods for
19 proceeding to a foreclosure sale, executing foreclosure
20 deeds, and filing foreclosure reports.
21 This bill would also make nonsubstantive,
22 technical revisions to update the existing code
23 language to current style.
24
25
26 A BILL
27 TO BE ENTITLED
28 AN ACT
Page 1

AN ACT
HB529 INTRODUCED
29
30 Relating to Class 2 municipalities; to amend Sections
31 11-40-65, 11-40-67, and 11-40-68, Code of Alabama 1975; to
32 remove the requirement to notify state and local taxing
33 authorities, other than the local ad valorem tax collector, of
34 the municipalities' intent to foreclose on a municipal lien;
35 to remove the requirement to use statutory language for
36 petitions for judicial in rem foreclosure and foreclosure
37 deeds; to authorize a Class 2 municipality to adopt its own
38 forms for petitions to foreclose and foreclosure deeds; to
39 authorize the municipality to proceed with a foreclosure sale
40 30 days from the date of the judicial order directing the sale
41 instead of 45 days; to authorize the circuit court to execute
42 foreclosure deeds within 30 days after the foreclosure sale
43 instead of 90 days; to authorize the municipality to file a
44 foreclosure report with the circuit clerk within 30 days of
45 the foreclosure sale instead of 90 days; and to make
46 nonsubstantive, technical revisions to update the existing
47 code language to current style.
48 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
49 Section 1. This act shall apply only to Class 2
50 municipalities.
51 Section 2. Sections 11-40-65, 11-40-67, and 11-40-68,
52 Code of Alabama 1975, are amended to read as follows:
